To my Fab Four! Thank you to each one of you for bringing your hearts and passion for our sport, demonstrating consistency in skills and leadership, and ALWAYS bringing your A game to every single practice. Coaches dream to have teams made of kids just like you…and your teammates will never forget the memories and impact you have had on their lives. These girls….MY GIRLS!!!! PROUD is understatement, HONORED to be by their side every step of the way, and READY to take on the future with them! They gave me everything they had this season! We took on a huge challenge to head back to @udadance Nationals for the first time in awhile with only one returner knowing just how exhausting and epic the competition is. It was an up and down rollercoaster of a week but they certainly held their own! In the end, I got to watch my Glitterbugs shine as they rallied out of the castle at finals (an experience you can’t imagine until you get to do it!) We came home with 7th in the Nation in the Large Pom Division against some of the highest level teams out there.  It’s an honor to continue to grow this incredible program along side our YL coaching staff, work with such passionate and talented dancers, and I’m always beyond grateful to have the most supportive families cheering us along all season! What an amazing season! I can’t believe it’s already time for our tryout meeting tonight! Head over to @ylhssong to find out details if you’d like to join this incredible team and program! Let’s get back at it girls! #lovemyglitterbugs #coachlife #mustangstampeed #dance #songleader

Happy Anniversary to all the Cheetahs out there! 20 years!!! Wow…I remember this day like it was yesterday. Anticipating the movie to premiere on the channel with an overwhelming feeling that I was a part of something bigger than just a movie, it was an empowering movement. I was given the chance to not only live out my dream but inspire others to reach for the stars. Encouraging them that anything was possible! Thank you all for taking the journey with us and continuously giving us so much love! We had the time of our lives traveling all around the world getting opportunities to meet so many of you and share our Cheetah Love! 
@debramchase thanks for taking a chance on this girl from Orange County, giving me the opportunity to live out my wildest dreams, and for being such a huge inspiration to me over the years!  To my Cheetahs @ravensymone @adriennebailon and @kielywilliams …just so incredibly grateful to share such a wild ride during our Cheetah journey with you all. The memories I will always cherish and the pride that fills me when looking back include all four of us and the special aspects each of us brought. Together we made magic that inspired generations of growl power! Ki, it would take pages and pages of words to describe how lucky I feel that what started out meeting a friend through work turned into a sister for life. We have shared so many ups and downs and been right by each others side through life’s biggest moments and our most cherished chapters. I love you so much and am so proud of the women, momma and friend you are! #cheetahloveforever

It’s coming up on 7 months postpartum for this girl! This is the point where the hair has fallen out (starting to grow back-insert ugly and uncontrollable fuzzies 😑) the body feels like it should be back to normal and it’s not, and your brain is telling you you should have it all together by now…spoiler alert…that is BS! With both babies this is the time during postpartum (6-7 months) where I have been hardest on myself. This time I caught myself and am doing a mind reset! I’m so lucky to have wonderful women that surround me with love and support, they remind me of all things that I AM and to give myself grace for the things I am still working on! 

As for the uncontrollable hair loss (a result from pregnancy) I had a momma-pro reach out to me about to fab products to help get my hair thicker, stronger, and longer to get me back in my hair whipping action asap! Huge thanks to @littlecupofjo for hooking this momma up! Dm her for a hair consult and she’ll send you a custom cart for your specific hair needs!!! #momshelpingmoms #momlife #postpartum #hairwhipsfordays

One thing my baby girl will always know is how AMAZING she is…not just to me but what she has to offer the world ! Do I want her to dance? YES! Will it kill me if she has other ideas…maybe a little bit (full truth…I’ll die inside just a tiny bit 🤷🏼‍♀️but live your life girl) but what I do know is she WILL do amazing things wherever she wants to go! It’s my job to teach her resilience when things do go the way you hoped for. She’ll know how to work hard, strive for better, and learn with every step!  No matter what she will always know mommy is right next to her and will always the best and loudest 😬cheerleader she’ll ever have in the crowd! Besides she’s a Cheetah Cub….all of the CHEETAH UNIVERSE has that extra sparkle!! Am I right??? #dailyaffirmations #cheetahlove #cheetahnextgen #cheetahnation #cheetah 

I will never step on a pedestal and preach like I know the best way about raising kids. This is me with my kiddo…doing the best I can 🤷🏼‍♀️
